      "content": "It's very likely that increased hydration is helping your body process the lithium, but persistent nausea and shaking suggest something more than just a slight adjustment. If you've been drinking a lot, try taking a small dose of a B-complex vitamin, as those can help with nerve function. If the shaking persists after a day of diligent hydration, you should definitely check in with your doctor about your current regimen.",
